The inflection of determinatives is complex, specially because of the high number of elisions, but is similar to the neighboring languages.{{sfn|Enciclopèdia Catalana|p=631}} Catalan has more contractions of preposition + article than [[Spanish language|Spanish]], like {{lang|ca|dels}} ("of + the [plural]"), but not as many as [[Italian language|Italian]] (which has {{lang|it|sul}}, {{lang|it|col}}, {{lang|it|nel}}, etc.).{{sfn|Enciclopèdia Catalana|p=631}}

Central Catalan has abandoned almost completely unstressed possessives ({{lang|ca|mon}}, etc.) in favour of constructions of article + stressed forms ({{lang|ca|el meu}}, etc.), a feature shared with Italian.{{sfn|Enciclopèdia Catalana|p=631}}

===Personal pronouns===
{| class="wikitable"  style="text-align:center; float:right;"
